719196f-a.title: Manhattan: Convent Avenue - 149th Street (West)
719196f-a.text:
Convent Avenue, east side, north across West 149th Street,
showing at the right, the Cosmosolital Tennis Club. This
is hidden behind the sign boards on the Avenue. View 2 is
limited to the antrance between the billboards.
May 19, 1940
No's. 1-2
P. L. Sperr
NO REPREODUCTIONS

719198f-a.title: Manhattan: Convent Avenue - 149th Street
719198f-a.text:
Convent Avenue, west side, from 150th to 149th Street.
Hamilton Grange Reformed Church is at the left in the background.
.t the right is 450-460 West 150th Street, at adjoining, and west of
the S.W. corner of Convent avenue. The six houses comprising the num-
hers from 450-460 are all 27Sstory frame houses.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 376
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON 2NL REPRODUCTIONS.
